# Cursor AI Rules for SEC 10-K Document Search Take-Home Project
# FastAPI + React/TypeScript + DuckDB Stack

## Project Overview
This project is a SEC 10-K document search application with:
- Backend: Python FastAPI with DuckDB for data storage
- Frontend: React/TypeScript with modern UI components
- Features: Company search, document browsing, hybrid search (FTS + Vector)
- Data: Pre-computed embeddings and full-text search capabilities

## Python/FastAPI Backend Rules

### Code Style & Structure
- Use Python 3.12+ features and type hints throughout
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines with 88-character line limit (Black formatting)
- Use descriptive variable and function names that clearly indicate purpose
- Implement proper error handling with custom exception classes
- Use Pydantic models for all API request/response validation
- Structure code with clear separation of concerns (models, services, routes)

### FastAPI Best Practices
- Use dependency injection for database connections and services
- Implement proper CORS middleware for frontend integration
- Use FastAPI's automatic OpenAPI documentation generation
- Implement proper HTTP status codes and error responses
- Use async/await patterns for I/O operations when beneficial
- Implement proper request validation with Pydantic models
- Use FastAPI's built-in security features for any authentication needs

### Database & DuckDB Integration
- Use connection pooling and proper connection management
- Implement proper transaction handling for data consistency
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Handle database locking scenarios gracefully (read-only connections when needed)
- Optimize queries for performance, especially for search operations
- Use proper indexing strategies for search performance

### Search Implementation
- Implement clean abstractions for different search engines (FTS, Vector, Hybrid)
- Use proper error handling for OpenAI API calls
- Implement fallback mechanisms when external services are unavailable
- Cache embeddings and search results when appropriate
- Use proper logging for search operations and performance monitoring

### Error Handling & Logging
- Use structured logging with appropriate log levels
- Implement comprehensive error handling with meaningful error messages
- Use custom exception classes for different error types
- Implement proper validation error responses
- Log performance metrics for search operations

## TypeScript/React Frontend Rules

### Component Architecture
- Use functional components with React hooks exclusively
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces for all props and state
- Use React.FC type annotation for components with props
- Implement custom hooks for reusable logic (API calls, state management)
- Use React.memo for performance optimization when needed
- Create reusable UI components with proper prop interfaces

### TypeScript Best Practices
- Use strict TypeScript configuration with no implicit any
- Implement proper type definitions for API responses
- Use union types and literal types for better type safety
- Implement proper error boundary components
- Use type inference where possible, explicit types where clarity is needed
- Create shared type definitions for API contracts

### State Management & Data Fetching
- Use useState and useEffect hooks appropriately
- Implement proper loading and error states for async operations
- Use proper dependency arrays in useEffect hooks
- Implement debouncing for search input fields
- Use proper state lifting and prop drilling patterns
- Consider using React Query or SWR for server state management

### UI/UX Implementation
- Implement responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Use semantic HTML elements for accessibility
- Implement proper loading indicators and skeleton screens
- Use proper form validation with user-friendly error messages
- Implement proper keyboard navigation and ARIA labels
- Use consistent spacing and typography throughout the application

### Performance Optimization
- Implement code splitting with React.lazy and Suspense
- Use proper key props in list rendering
- Implement virtualization for large lists when needed
- Optimize bundle size with proper import strategies
- Use proper image optimization techniques
- Implement proper caching strategies for API calls

## Project-Specific Guidelines

### API Integration
- Create a centralized API client with proper error handling
- Implement proper TypeScript types for all API endpoints
- Use consistent error handling patterns across all API calls
- Implement proper request/response logging for debugging
- Use proper HTTP methods and status codes

### Search Functionality
- Implement proper search result highlighting
- Use debounced search input to avoid excessive API calls
- Implement proper search history and suggestions
- Use proper pagination for search results
- Implement proper search filters and sorting options

### Document Handling
- Implement proper document preview functionality
- Use proper file type handling and validation
- Implement proper document metadata display
- Use proper document navigation and breadcrumbs
- Implement proper document sharing and linking

### Testing Strategy
- Write unit tests for utility functions and business logic
- Implement integration tests for API endpoints
- Use proper mocking strategies for external dependencies
- Implement proper test data management
- Use proper test coverage reporting

### Development Workflow
- Use proper Git commit message conventions
- Implement proper code review practices
- Use proper environment variable management
- Implement proper development/production configuration
- Use proper dependency management and version pinning

## Code Quality Standards
- Maintain high code coverage with meaningful tests
- Use proper linting and formatting tools (ESLint, Prettier, Black, isort)
- Implement proper pre-commit hooks for code quality
- Use proper documentation for complex business logic
- Implement proper performance monitoring and metrics
- Follow security best practices for data handling

## Additional Instructions
1. Always prioritize code readability and maintainability
2. Implement proper error boundaries and fallback UI components
3. Use proper loading states and skeleton screens for better UX
4. Implement proper accessibility features (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)
5. Use proper semantic versioning for any package updates
6. Implement proper monitoring and alerting for production issues
7. Follow the existing project structure and naming conventions
8. Prioritize performance optimization for search operations
9. Implement proper data validation on both frontend and backend
10. Use proper security practices for any sensitive data handling


